features:
	1.record full filenames that opened by vim/gvim
		## most recent file recorded by lowest index
	2.can record maximum 50 filenames
	3.can easily reopen the recorded file by specifying the corresponding index
		# vimshell -r <index>
	4.display recorded file information:
		# vimshell -l
		# which will display file list like:
			# [1] /fullPath/filename2
			# [0] /fullPath/filename
	5.TBD, reserved for later versions
